T1  - A semiparametric structural analysis of the idling of cement kilns
AU  - Das, Sanghamitra
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 50
IS  - 3
SP  - 235
EP  - 256
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/12/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(91)90020-E
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769190020E
AB  - This paper estimates the decision rule for idling capital at the micro (firm) level. This is done for a cement kiln by using data from the US cement industry. The decision rule for not operating a kiln at a given point in time is the standard rule: do not operate if the average variable cost exceeds price. The parameters of this discrete-decision rule are semiparametrically estimated using the maximum-score method and the estimates are then compared with the logit maximum-likelihood estimates in terms of their values as well as predictions.
